->What is Flutter?
Flutter is an open source software development kit (SDK) UI used for cross-platform applications 
from a single codebase. 
Flutter is primarily used for creating natively compiled, multi-platform applications across iOS 
and Android seamlessly.


->What is Dart?
Dart is a general-purpose, object-oriented programming language that was initially developed by 
Google in 2011. 
It is designed to be fast, efficient, and scalable, making it ideal for building a wide range of 
applications, including web and mobile apps, server-side applications, and command-line tools.

